RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 12000. Non-winners of a race since April 7 Allowed 2 lbs. Claimin g Price $5,000 (Claiming races for $4,000 or less not considered in estimating allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMILE AT THE STORM broke awkwardly, quickly recovered, sent to a clear lead and held safe in the drive under strong encouragement. TAP N TWINE was coaxed along from the inside, raced two to four wide in the stretch run and finished willingly to the wire. SUPERSTAR DIVA was bumped at the start, chased the leaders from the two path and kept on to the wire racing four deep. FANCY EMPRESS was slow early on, raced four wide around the far turn and lacked a solid rally raced three deep. ARCH FLYER settled early on, raced along the inside around the far into the upper stretch and lacked a bid. BAILESTON LASSIE dropped back off the early pace, was three deep past the quarter pole and never had a response while racing from the outside.

ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, inside upper stretch, lacked bid
